FBIS4-55787 "dreeu098__a94034" FBIS-EEU-94-098-A Daily Report 18 May 1994 ANNEX Yugoslavia, Kosovo Serb Soldiers on Border Ban Farming Work Serb Soldiers on Border Ban Farming Work AU1805195294 Tirana ATA in English 1016 GMT 18 May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1805195294 Tirana ATA English BFN [Text] Prishtina, May 18 (ATA) -- A considerable number of Serb soldiers are deployed recently in the border area between Albania and Kosova so banning the Albanian farmers from using the pasture land. They have declared it "forbidden area," because it is near the border zone. The army has blocked the roads that lead to the pasture land and conducts a severe search, prohibiting so the free pass of people. Against such measures, have reacted the Albanian political subjects of Decan commune and has appealed to the farmers to be cautious not to fall into the trap of the Serb militaries.
